article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 97, N. Illinois 85
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Steven Moore scored a season-high 22 points to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to a 97-85 victory over Northern Illinois on Sunday. UALR (7-2) shot 61.8 percent from the field and had six players scored in double digits. Darion Anderson had 29 points for Northern Illinois (4-6). UALR led 43-23 at halftime. NIU was unable to get closer than 10 points with 27 seconds left to play. Brandon Patterson recorded his first career double-double with 10 points and a career-high 10 rebounds for the Trojans, while Matt Mouzy added 14 points and John Fowler, Mike Smith and Curtis Jackson each had 10. Najul Ervin had 11 points, seven rebounds and four steals for the Huskies.
